{"id":"broadside-r9da.58","title":"content.rs: overlapping-replacement dedup keeps wrong replacement","description":"LOCATION: src/content.rs:130-136, process_content()

FINDING: The dedup logic iterates replacements sorted by start position descending and keeps a replacement only if its end <= the previous (higher-start) replacement's start. But the loop variable is 'r' (the current, lower-start entry) and 'prev' is the already-kept higher-start entry. The condition 'r.1 <= prev.0' compares the current replacement's END against the previously kept replacement's START. When a URL match and a hashtag match partially overlap (e.g. a URL ending in '#tag'), the URL replacement that starts earlier will be dropped and the hashtag replacement kept — even though the URL match has priority by virtue of appearing first. More critically, if two replacements have overlapping spans but neither fully contains the other, both can be emitted and result.replace_range panics on an out-of-order or overlapping range.

IMPACT: Possible panic (index out of bounds on replace_range) when content contains a URL whose tail overlaps the # of a hashtag, e.g. 'https://example.com/page#rust'. The URL regex captures 'https://example.com/page#rust' and the hashtag regex captures '#rust' from within it; after sorting and filtering, both pass the overlap check because the logic tests r.1 <= prev.0 (end of URL <= start of hashtag?) not r.1 <= prev.1.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","owner":"mark@reviewcommit.com","created_at":"2026-07-20T01:55:43.734258306Z","created_by":"Mark Atwood","updated_at":"2026-07-20T01:55:43.734258306Z","labels":["correctness","review"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"broadside-r9da.58","depends_on_id":"broadside-r9da","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-07-20T01:55:43.767023746Z","created_by":"Mark Atwood","metadata":"{}"}]}
